===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈlɪŋ.ɡwə fɹæŋ.kə/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[lingua]] [[franca]]}}

# a common language used by people of diverse backgrounds to communicate with one another, often a basic form of speech with simplified grammar

====Usage notes====
* The most common plural form in English is {{term|lingua francas|lang=en}}; however, the plural forms {{term|lingue franche|lang=en}} (following the Italian) and {{term|linguae francae|lang=en}} (in the style of Latin) are both fairly common as well. Also attested, but quite rare, and probably nonstandard, is the form {{term|linguas franca|lang=en}} (treating {{term||lingua|lang=en}} alone as the noun and taking {{term||franca|lang=en}} as an adjective; compare {{term|attorney general|attorneys general|lang=en}}, {{term|forest primeval|forests primeval}}).

